  <prompt>
    Build `ExecutionTraceWidget.tsx` as a Context-pane widget that subscribes to all six
    new `context.*` event types from task 059 and renders an ordered timeline of the
    chat agent's reasoning steps — modeled on the Claude Code execution-trace surface.
    Each event renders as a timeline entry: tool calls show tool name + decision + timing;
    knowledge retrievals show source ID + relevance score; playbook node executions show
    node ID + status; decisions show decision string + brief reason. Built in
    `@spaarke/ai-widgets` per ADR-012; Fluent v9 components; light + dark mode parity
    per ADR-021. Auto-scrolls on new events. Collapsible per-event-type filter.

    **ADR-015 BINDING (CRITICAL)**: render only the typed fields from the event payload.
    NEVER attempt to render free-form content. NEVER call any "show me the user
    message" affordance — the widget is observability of agent reasoning, not
    transcript replay.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React/Fluent-v9 engineer with familiarity with PaneEventBus subscription
    patterns + Context-pane widget registry + Claude Code transparency UX reference.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Widget renders in Context pane; subscribes to `context.*` events; timeline auto-scrolls
    on new events; collapsible filters work; light + dark parity verified; ADR-015 audit
    confirms no free-form content rendering.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
